  "feedback": "## Iter-4 Review — Issue #615 GUI Role Selector Parity\n\n**Scope**: `src/clawrium/gui/routes/providers.py` + `gui/` frontend only.\n\n---\n\n### Aggregate Rating: **2/5** (test-coverage blockers gate merge)\n\n---\n\n## Blocking Issues\n\n### B1 — Persist-failure path untested (`tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py`)\n`fake_update_host` always returns `True` in every fixture. The `_persist_attachments` branch at `providers.py:422-425` (`if not update_host(...): raise HTTPException(500, ...)`) has zero coverage. This is a new code path introduced in this PR.\n\n**Fix**: Add `test_attach_persist_failure_returns_500` — patch `fake_update_host` to return `False`, assert `HTTPException(status_code=500)` with `'failed to persist'` in detail. Mirror for detach.\n\n### B2 — Detach-rejection missing state-unchanged assertion (`tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py:465-478`)\nThe attach path's B3 fix adds `assert len(state[...][providers]) == 2` after rejection. `test_detach_primary_with_aux_remaining_rejected` and `test_detach_primary_409_lists_blocking_aux_names` lack the symmetric assertion — a future refactor that lets persist run before the guard would not be caught.\n\n**Fix**: Add `assert len(state[\"host\"][\"agents\"][\"sage\"][\"providers\"]) == 2` immediately after the `pytest.raises` blocks in both detach-rejection tests.\n\n---\n\n## Warnings\n\n### W-A — TOCTOU race on concurrent attaches (`providers.py:524-595`, already noted as code W3)\nThe conflict check reads `current` outside `update_host`'s write lock. Two concurrent POSTs can both pass the occupant check and clobber each other silently. The code already tracks this at lines 566-571 with a follow-up reference. Confirm that follow-up issue exists and is linked before merging.\n\n### W-B — `_attachment_name(occupant)` can return `None` (`providers.py:585-593`)\nIf the occupant dict has no `name` key, the 409 detail renders `None` rather than the provider name. Guard: `occ_name = _attachment_name(occupant); if occ_name is not None and occ_name != name:` and use `occ_name` in the f-string.\n\n### W-C — Frontend `saving=true` / `error` / `attachments=null` states uncovered (`attach-provider-modal.test.tsx`)\nThree real user-visible states have no test: (1) `saving=true` → button disabled + \"Attaching…\" text; (2) `error` prop → `role=\"alert\"` element; (3) `attachments=null` → null-coalescing defaults. Add three targeted tests.\n\n### W-D — `role=\"alert\"` missing on slots-filled paragraph (`attach-provider-modal.tsx:119`)\nThe \"All auxiliary slots are filled\" `\u003cp\u003e` has no `role=\"alert\"` or `aria-live`. Consistent with the existing error paragraph at line 151 which does carry it. One-line fix: `\u003cp role=\"alert\" className=\"text-xs text-amber-700\"\u003e`.\n\n---\n\n## Clean / Confirmed\n\n| Item | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Orphan `\u003clabel htmlFor=roleId\u003e` fix | ✅ Logically correct — label and select gate on identical `!noAvailableRoles` condition |\n| Modal close paths all route through `handleClose` (state reset) | ✅ Confirmed |\n| 409 body exposes only provider names, no credentials | ✅ Confirmed |\n| `body.role != PRIMARY_ROLE` guard removal doesn't open bypass | ✅ Conflict check now symmetric for primary and auxiliary slots |\n| Role field validated against `VALID_ROLES` before conflict check | ✅ Confirmed |\n| B3 state-unchanged assertion (attach path) | ✅ Real and meaningful |\n| `noAvailableRoles` conditional render branch coverage | ✅ Fully exercised in tests |\n| 409 conflict guard: success + negative path coverage | ✅ Including new primary-slot symmetric test |\n| W2 TODO placement (`agent-attachments-card.tsx:174`) | ✅ Actionable, correct call site |\n| CLI tests for #616 out of scope | ✅ Confirmed, not needed here |\n\n---\n\n## Required Before Merge\n\n1. **Add `test_attach_persist_failure_returns_500` + mirror for detach** (B1)\n2. **Add state-unchanged `len == 2` assertion to both detach-rejection tests** (B2)\n3. **Confirm W3/W4 follow-up TODOs in `providers.py` have linked issue numbers** (TOCTOU race + structured 409 body)\n\nAddressing W-B (`_attachment_name` null guard), W-C (three frontend tests), and W-D (`role=\"alert\"`) is strongly recommended but not merge-blocking per ATX threshold.\n",
