      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 4,\n  \"summary\": \"The orphan-label fix is logically correct and well-tested. Label and select gate on the same `!noAvailableRoles` condition, the three close paths in Modal all route through handleClose (state reset guaranteed), and the disabled-button guard covers every noAvailableRoles branch. One suggestion on the slots-filled paragraph and one observation about the W3/W4 TODO scope.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.tsx:119\",\n      \"issue\": \"The `\u003cp\u003e` 'All auxiliary slots are filled' has no `role=\\\"alert\\\"` or `aria-live` attribute. If attachments fill up while the modal is already open (e.g., a concurrent attach on another session triggers a refetch), AT users won't be notified of the state change. The submit button being disabled is the only signal they get.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `role=\\\"alert\\\"` to the paragraph: `\u003cp role=\\\"alert\\\" className=\\\"text-xs text-amber-700\\\"\u003e`. This is low-cost and consistent with the existing `role=\\\"alert\\\"` on the error paragraph at line 151.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.tsx:105-148\",\n      \"issue\": \"The label/select conditional structure uses two separate guards (`!noAvailableRoles` for the label, the ternary for select/paragraph). They are logically equivalent and produce correct output, but the double-gate is slightly harder to audit — a future editor could change one without the other.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Low priority, no action required. Alternatively, group label + select into a single fragment under `!noAvailableRoles` and keep only the paragraph in the `else` branch. This makes the coupling explicit. Current code is not wrong.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/agent-attachments-card.tsx:174\",\n      \"issue\": \"W2 TODO comment is well-placed and actionable (`aria-describedby + sr-only span` deferral). No issue with placement or wording.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"No action needed. Confirmed correct call site and deferral language.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"commit message (a138ffa)\",\n      \"issue\": \"W3/W4 TODO comments referenced in the commit message are in `src/clawrium/gui/routes/providers.py`, which is the Python backend route — outside the `gui/` frontend scope of this review. Cannot verify their placement or actionability in this pass.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Confirm W3 (TOCTOU slot-conflict race) and W4 (structured 409 body) TODOs are present and have follow-up issue references in providers.py before closing this iter.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add `role=\\\"alert\\\"` to the 'All auxiliary slots are filled' paragraph (attach-provider-modal.tsx:119) — one-line fix, closes the only remaining AT gap in the modal itself.\",\n    \"Verify W3/W4 TODO comments in providers.py have linked follow-up issue numbers; if not, add them before merging.\",\n    \"No blocking issues. Component is ready to merge after the role=\\\"alert\\\" suggestion is evaluated.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 4,\n    \"domain\": \"gui/frontend — React/TSX modal component, types, tests\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
