) == 2` immediately after the pytest.raises block in test_detach_primary_with_aux_remaining_rejected. Also add to test_detach_primary_409_lists_blocking_aux_names (line 522).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py:609-614,668-672\",\n      \"issue\": \"The except AttachmentError -\u003e HTTP 400 backstop in attach_provider_to_agent (line 613) and detach_provider_from_agent (line 671) is dead code in CI. The pre-validate guards (role not in VALID_ROLES, slot-conflict check, singleton check) intercept all reachable paths before validate() can raise. No test exercises these branches. The comment in test_attach_hermes_http_all_aux_filled_rejects_via_validate even notes 'AttachmentError from validate() is a backstop only' — meaning the backstop itself is never tested.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Either add a test that directly calls _persist_attachments with a malformed attachment list to exercise the AttachmentError path, or document the branches as intentionally unreachable with a # pragma: no cover annotation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.test.tsx\",\n      \"issue\": \"Three props that drive meaningful UI state have no test: (1) saving=true should disable the Attach button and render 'Attaching…' text — no test; (2) error prop should render a role=alert element with the error string — no test; (3) attachments=null (loading/error state) exercises the `?? false` and `?? []` defaults but has no test — a refactor that changes the null-coalescing path would pass silently.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add three tests: one rendering with saving=true asserting getByText('Attaching…') and button.disabled; one rendering with error='some error' asserting getByRole('alert') contains the string; one rendering with attachments={null} asserting no Role selector and Attach is disabled.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.test.tsx\",\n      \"issue\": \"The auto-pin hint ('Only one role is available — this attach will be locked to primary') rendered at lines 141-147 of attach-provider-modal.tsx has no test. The existing 'hermes first attach' test correctly asserts the select is disabled but does not assert this hint text is shown.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Extend the 'pins role to primary' test to also assert getByText(/locked to/i) is present when availableRoles.length === 1.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py: Add test_attach_persist_failure_returns_500 — patch fake_update_host to return False, assert HTTPException(500) from attach_provider_to_agent. Mirror for detach. This unblocks the persist failure-path gap (B1).\",\n    \"tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py: Add state-unchanged assertion (len == 2) to test_detach_primary_with_aux_remaining_rejected and test_detach_primary_409_lists_blocking_aux_names to match the symmetry established by the attach B3 fix (B2).\",\n    \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.test.tsx: Add tests for saving=true (button state), error prop (alert render), and attachments=null (null-coalescing defaults) — these cover real user-visible states that currently have no coverage.\",\n    \"CLI tests for #616 (clawctl agent provider attach/detach) are explicitly out of scope for this review and are not needed here — confirmed.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 5,\n    \"domain\": \"test-coverage\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
